I read the reviews, and I disagree... I would not say the ingredients are bland. I would say they use very fresh ingredients, fast service and above all... really good pricing. The people in the reviews who give it 1 star for being bland... well that’s not fair. Even if it was bland, it’s $7 for a giant burrito in nyc which is almost unheard of. I can’t speak to their customer service because I haven’t had an issue, which is actually a good thing. Their menu is robust, especially for burritos. My Mexican delivery guy introduced it to me... and well, he’s from Mexico City born and raised. Never heard him complain! Just wanted to show my support. Too often people only review something when it’s bad, just here to show I also give good reviews. I won’t give them 5 stars because I want this to be honest. Is it the most gourmet Mexican food in nyc? No. But boy it beats Chipotle and most other small businesses pedaling even worse quality for higher prices. Bottom line is... they have an extremely affordable menu and I know for a fact it is Mexican approved. Great work!

Even the guacamole somehow lacked the magical bliss that guacamole usually possesses...truly a Herculean feat.  Marinated (really?) chicken tacos: bland and soggy. Guacamole: bland and watery. Street corn: utterly drenched in mayo.  If you like Mexican food for its flavor and spiciness, you won’t find that here.
